title: Henryville Classic Road Race
description: The Henryville Classic Road Race is the second raceof the Kentuckiana Spring Training Series. Competitors earn points in each race to compete for Overall series standings.
course: Course is a 14 mile loop with a mixture of rolling and flat terrain on well maintained rual roads in Clark County Indiana.
registration: On-line registration at www.TrueSport.com.  Late or day-of registration is an additional $10
notes: Check www.KyAnaSeries.com for more information and series standings as well as cancellation information.  Races held rain or shine.  Pay-out and result posting at finish line.
directions:
From I-65 north: exit #19 Henryville.  Turn right after exit onto Hwy 160 east.  Turn left at stop sign onto Hwy 31 north.  Turn left into Henryville High school for registration

From I-65 south: exit #19 Henryville.  Turn left after exit onto Hwy 160 east.  Turn left at stop sign onto Hwy 31 north.  Turn left into Henryville High school for registration
